## 3. Free Stock Price APIs (2026)

**Confidence: HIGH** — multiple 2025/2026 comparison sources agree.

For ~7 tickers at 15-minute intervals: that's 7 requests every 15 minutes = 28 requests/hour = 672 requests/day (market hours only). Add historical and health checks and you're at ~800/day.

| API | Free Daily Limit | Reliability | Notes |
|-----|-----------------|-------------|-------|
| **Twelve Data** | 800 calls/day, 8 req/min | 99.95% uptime | **Best choice** |
| Financial Modeling Prep | 250 calls/day | Reliable | Better for fundamentals than quotes |
| Alpha Vantage | 25 calls/day | Solid data quality | Completely unusable for polling |
| Yahoo Finance | Unofficial / no limit | Breaks randomly | ToS violation, not recommended |
| Finnhub | 60 req/min (very generous) | Good | Free tier has WebSocket too |

**Recommendation: Twelve Data** for your specific use case.

7 tickers at 15-min polling fits exactly within the 800 call/day free tier with room for retries. The endpoint is clean:

```js
// Twelve Data quote endpoint
async function fetchQuote(symbol) {
  const res = await fetch(
    `https://api.twelvedata.com/quote?symbol=${symbol}&apikey=${import.meta.env.VITE_TWELVE_DATA_KEY}`
  );
  return res.json();
}

// Batch fetch — Twelve Data supports comma-separated symbols in one call
async function fetchBatchQuotes(symbols) {
  const symbolStr = symbols.join(',');  // e.g., "AAPL,MSFT,GOOGL"
  const res = await fetch(
    `https://api.twelvedata.com/quote?symbol=${symbolStr}&apikey=${import.meta.env.VITE_TWELVE_DATA_KEY}`
  );
  return res.json();  // returns object keyed by symbol when batch
}
```

Twelve Data supports batch symbol queries (comma-separated) in a single API call, which means your 7 tickers can be 1 request per interval instead of 7. That drops your daily usage from ~672 to ~96 calls — well within free tier.

**Finnhub** is worth a look too — 60 req/min free, WebSocket streaming available. If you want realtime push instead of polling, Finnhub's free WebSocket is the option.

